## Remarks  
 <span data-ttu-id="60098-102">Wenn sie ausgelöst werden, die <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognitionEngine.AudioLevelUpdated?displayProperty=nameWithType> und <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognizer.AudioLevelUpdated?displayProperty=nameWithType> Ereignisse übergeben Sie eine Instanz des <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.AudioLevelUpdatedEventArgs> an den Handler für das zugeordnete Ereignis.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="60098-102">When they are raised, the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognitionEngine.AudioLevelUpdated?displayProperty=nameWithType> and <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognizer.AudioLevelUpdated?displayProperty=nameWithType> events pass an instance of  <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.AudioLevelUpdatedEventArgs> to  the handler for the associated event.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="60098-103">Die <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.AudioLevelUpdatedEventArgs.AudioLevel%2A> Eigenschaft ruft der neue Pegel der Audioeingabe, wenn eingeben die <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognitionEngine.AudioLevelUpdated?displayProperty=nameWithType> oder <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognizer.AudioLevelUpdated?displayProperty=nameWithType> Ereignis wird ausgelöst.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="60098-103">The <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.AudioLevelUpdatedEventArgs.AudioLevel%2A> property gets the new level of audio input when the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognitionEngine.AudioLevelUpdated?displayProperty=nameWithType> or <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognizer.AudioLevelUpdated?displayProperty=nameWithType> event is raised.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="60098-104">Die `AudioLevel` Eigenschaft der <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognizer> und <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognitionEngine> Klassen bereitstellt, die aktuelle Ebene der Audioeingabe für die spracherkennungs-Engine.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="60098-104">The `AudioLevel` property of the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognizer> and <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognitionEngine> classes provides the current level of the audio input to the speech recognition engine.</span></span>  
  
   
  
## Examples  
 <span data-ttu-id="60098-105">Das folgende Beispiel fügt einen Ereignishandler an ein <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognitionEngine> Objekt.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="60098-105">The following example adds an event handler to a <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognitionEngine> object.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="60098-106">Der Handler gibt die neue Audiodatei Ebene in der Konsole aus.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="60098-106">The handler outputs the new audio level to the console.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="60098-107"><xref:System.Speech.Recognition.AudioLevelUpdatedEventArgs> wird von <xref:System.EventArgs> abgeleitet.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="60098-107"><xref:System.Speech.Recognition.AudioLevelUpdatedEventArgs> derives from <xref:System.EventArgs>.</span></span>  
  
```csharp  
  
private SpeechRecognitionEngine sre;  
  
// Initialize the SpeechRecognitionEngine object.   
private void Initialize()  
{  
  sre = new SpeechRecognitionEngine();  
  
  // Add an event handler for the AudioLevelUpdated event.  
  sre.AudioLevelUpdated += new EventHandler<AudioLevelUpdatedEventArgs>(sre_AudioLevelUpdated);  
  
  // Add other initialization code here.  
}  
  
// Write the audio level to the console when the AudioLevelUpdated event is raised.  
void sre_AudioLevelUpdated(object sender, AudioLevelUpdatedEventArgs e)  
{  
  Console.WriteLine("The audio level is now: {0}.", e.AudioLevel);  
}  
  
```
